open educational resources (oer) are free materials you can use in your courses. using these resources has several important benefits to you and your students: not only is cost an important issue, but oer is part of a global initiative to expand educational access for all underserved populations.     in addition to ecampus, there are five other great resources to help you successfully incorporate oer in your course. sjsu library oer resources by college csu affordable learning solutions - visit this website to find all kinds of open materials; free textbooks, individual modules, or whole courses. your contacts at the sjsu king library are: email: adriana.poo@sjsu.edu phone: 1-408-808-2019 email: christa.bailey@sjsu.edu phone: 1-408-808-242 phone: 408-924-2337 email: ecampus@sjsu.edu location: irc, room 206 ecampus, irc206 instructional resource center san jose state university one washington square san jose, ca 95192-0026 